@startuml
title Scan Initiation - C# API to Redis Queue

actor User as U
participant "Next.js Frontend" as FE
participant "C# API Controller" as Controller
participant "Scan Handler" as Handler
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
participant "Redis Producer" as Producer
participant "Redis Queue" as Redis

U -> FE: 1. Click "Run Scan"
FE -> Controller: 2. POST /api/domains/{id}/scans
Controller -> Handler: 3. CreateScanCommand(id, user_id)
Handler -> DB: 4. Verify domain ownership
DB --> Handler: 5. Domain is verified

Handler -> DB: 6. INSERT INTO scans (status='queued')
DB --> Handler: 7. Return scan_id

Handler -> Handler: 8. Create ScanJob payload
note right
  {
    "scan_id": "abc-123",
    "domain": "example.com",
    "user_id": "user-456"
  }
end note

Handler -> Producer: 9. Publish to Redis
Producer -> Redis: 10. LPUSH scan:queue
Redis --> Producer: 11. Acknowledged

Handler --> Controller: 12. Return scan_id
Controller --> FE: 13. 202 Accepted
FE -> FE: 14. Start polling
FE --> U: 15. "Scan queued"

@enduml